				<h2 class="title icon">
					<img src="http://forum.opiophile.org/images/icons/icon6.gif" alt="Default" /> Re: First time with methadone--how much to take?
				</h2>
				


						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_38859">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/Eloquent/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>poppy</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?s=31fe3f4be566a1cc7ad85fefb005b8f3&amp;p=38742#post38742" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/Eloquent/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">What do you guys mean by a 'wafer'. In the past eight years I've been prescribed methadone in various forms: injectable amps, oral mixture (medicine), and tablets, but I have never come across this 'wafer' which I've heard so many of you guys over the pond describe?<br />
PS Adormidera, Think long and hard before taking methadone, its a tough drug to get off believe me!! I thought the withdrawals from heroin were hard until I tried to kick meth!!!</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>                                Poppy we have wafers over here which are flat pills about as big as an american dime ,that has a  +  on it therefore you can split it up four ways.10 milligrams a dose.Picture a circle with a plus sign in it and each time you break off a triangle you are getting 10 milligrams if you eat half a wafer you are eating 20 milligrams.A whole wafer is 40 milligrams.<br />
                                These pills also dissolve very quickly in water,juice or any beverage that is what most people do with it,although I imagine this form of the drug is easier also to inject.<br />
                                    I get the 10 milligram ones which don't dissolve in water and they are full of fillers,but I don't want to inject my morphine anyways.<br />
                                     Unlike where you live we don't get the injectable methadone but we do get the liquid,the pills and the wafers,I hope this helps.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
